title: Space Force sees room for more competitors in national security launch
summary: Gen. John Raymond said the  the Space Force might consider working with more than two launch companies as more players enter the industry

title: NASA Chooses Small Businesses to Continue Exploration Tech Development
summary: NASA's Small Business Innovation Research (SBIR) program has chosen 110 U.S. small businesses for continued technology development.

title: James Webb telescope completes optical alignment, ready for final instrument calibration phase of commissioning
summary: The James Webb Space Telescope (JWST) has entered a new phase of its commissioning process as NASA announces that the observatory has completed its mirror alignment and focusing process and is ready to move into the instrument calibration ahead of full science operations later this year.

title: Watch live: Russian cosmonauts begin 250th space station spacewalk
summary: Russian cosmonauts Oleg Artemyev and Denis Matveev ventured outside the International Space Station on Thursday for a planned six-and-a-half hour spacewalk to begin unlimbering the European Robotic Arm.

title: Northrop Grumman expects a $2 billion order from ULA for solid rocket boosters
summary: Northrop Grumman is anticipating a $2 billion contract from United Launch Alliance for solid rocket boosters, president and CEO Kathy Warden said April 28.
